  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nI am trying to enable fingerprint login on my Status app.\r\nMy account is setup with a keycard.\r\nI find the flow confusing and I am not able to reach a stage where my app is locked and I am able to unlock it with a fingerprint.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. In Privacy & Security I have \"Lock app with fingerprint\" on\r\n2. The only way to lock the app seems to do profile > sign out\r\n3. This gives a \"log out\" confirmation (Maybe better to keen same terminology across the screens? log out < sign out).\r\n4. tap log out\r\n5. To sign in, I have to enter my pin, \"don't ask for card to sign in\" is unchecked.\r\n6. I check \"don't ask for card to sign in\" > pop ups to secure with fingerprint shows up\r\n7. Tap enable fingerprint\r\n8. touch sensor\r\n9. \"don't ask for card to sign in\" is now ticked\r\n10. enter pin\r\n11. It ask for keycard, scan keycard\r\n12. Logged in\r\n13. Again, only way to lock the card I can see is \"Sign out\"\r\n14. \"Are you sure you want to log out?\"\r\n15. log out\r\n16. back to log in screen where the \"don't ask for card to sign in\" is unchecked\r\n17. Enter pin\r\n18. Asks for keycard\r\n\r\nI'd expect to be able to just scan with my fingerprint at steps 5 and 16.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: 1.16.0\r\n- Operating System: Android\r\n",
